    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-08-11T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-08-11T18:00:00-05:00" n="521"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d521">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.6354/287a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-08-11T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 11, 1941—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3085. The Department has been informed that the Bolivian delegates to the
                    International Tin Conference (Señores Antenor Patiño and Jorge Ortiz-Linares)
                    are leaving by clipper on August 16 to participate in the forthcoming
                    discussions, which, it is assumed, will center about the allocation of quotas
                    for the coming year. The Embassy is requested to render all appropriate advice
                    and assistance to the Bolivian delegates. The position of the Department with
                    respect to the Bolivian quota was outlined in the Department’s 778 of March 8,
                    1941, 7 p.m., and this attitude is reaffirmed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
